 add the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and give it the new theme object.","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Project must compile then. This is until today (API 0.20.0) the only way to instanciated and inject a theme.","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-2-2.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-2-2.png"}],"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS must be used in SwiftUI projects.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We suppose you already have an app or a freshly created new one, with OUDS Swift Package integrated and the librairies added to the target.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"We supposed also you have Xcode 26.4 at least, and for example an iPhone 17 Pro Max simulator.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Source code and tokens here are the ones of version 0.20.0 ; things can change in the future.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"title":"Basic structure for the app","anchor":"Basic-structure-for-the-app"}],"kind":"tasks"},{"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"type":"multiple-choice","content":[],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Is it mandatory to use today the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"text":"?","type":"text"}]}],"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is! Otherwise the theme won’t be defined and available as environment variable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No"}]}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" is mandatory to inject as environment variable the theme and expose it in every view inside."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"assessments"},{"title":"Use your first OUDS components","abstract":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use.","type":"text"}],"action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components","overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}]},"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","kind":"callToAction"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Want-to-be-an-artist":{"abstract":[{"text":"Even if components increase the identity of your apps, it is not enough. Typography, fonts and tokens are here to improve that.","type":"text"}],"title":"Want to be an artist?","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Want-to-be-an-artist","role":"pseudoSymbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Want-to-be-an-artist","type":"section","kind":"section"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding":{"type":"link","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check Your Understanding"}],"title":"Check Your Understanding"},"doc://OUDSThemesCont